{"TopicId":210727,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Carl Sagan Space Telescope","CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-21T18:33:39Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-21T18:33:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTentative announcement of a planned Hubble/JWST successor. \u00A0 \u00A020m mirror, observes in the optical spectrum. \u00A0 It\u2019s main goal is direct imaging of exoplanets. \u00A0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/BIgQpXObjFI?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022JWST\u0027s successor: The Carl Sagan Observatory - a 12 METRE optical telescope searching for exo-Earth\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-21T19:16:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n20m, so, $20B? Hopefully they can use some lessons learned from Webb to speed it up and keep costs down\u2026\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-21T20:06:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224201206\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210727\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221669058183\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n56 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n20m, so, $20B? Hopefully they can use some lessons learned from Webb to speed it up and keep costs down\u2026\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPresuming SS gets working... they have heavy lift available they don\u0027t / won\u0027t have to wait for...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo - maybe, possibly, it could be on time?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-11-21T20:13:30Z\u0022 title=\u002211/21/2022 08:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 21, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by JoeSchmuckatelli\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-21T22:00:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224201206\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210727\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221669058183\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n20m, so, $20B? Hopefully they can use some lessons learned from Webb to speed it up and keep costs down\u2026\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was one of the topics she talked about in the video, how the talent and knowledge is already in the work force to make this type of telescope, and since the majority of it won\u0027t be inventing the wheel again, the costs and production issues should be kept to a \u0022minimum\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-22T03:16:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo optical scopes require the same cryogenic requirements as the webb?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-22T03:19:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224201337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210727\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221669086985\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nuke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Nuke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo optical scopes require the same cryogenic requirements as the webb?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would not think so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://webb.nasa.gov/content/about/innovations/cryocooler.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ECryocooler Webb/NASA\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHubble has one too - but it\u0027s to allow the NICMOS to see IR.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://aip.scitation.org/doi/pdf/10.1063/1.2908673\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ETHE NICMOS COOLING SYSTEM\u20145 YEARS OF SUCCESSFUL ON-ORBIT OPERATION (scitation.org)\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: so maybe, depending upon feature creep.\u00A0 For pure optical, I doubt it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-11-22T03:23:54Z\u0022 title=\u002211/22/2022 03:23  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 22, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by JoeSchmuckatelli\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Minmus Taster","CreatedById":206159,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-22T17:13:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224201337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210727\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221669086985\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nuke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Nuke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo optical scopes require the same cryogenic requirements as the webb?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInfrared requires more cooling, a telescope like Carl Sagan would need a larger shield but not as many layers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UmbralRaptor","CreatedById":2767,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-23T06:12:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConsidering that the decadal survey shot down LUVOIR for cost reasons and ended up recommending something intermediate in size between HabEx and LUVOIR for the 2040s, I have doubts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-23T14:45:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA saganscope should be able to find and observe the planets with nuclear winter, so it should have rather sensitive IR channel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-23T17:17:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224201601\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210727\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221669183943\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222767\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UmbralRaptor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, UmbralRaptor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConsidering that the decadal survey shot down LUVOIR for cost reasons and ended up recommending something intermediate in size between HabEx and LUVOIR for the 2040s, I have doubts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDecadal survey came out before the JWST launch, didn\u0027t it?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFans and hype (and success) change priorities.\u00A0 The non-science-nerd excitement over Webb images does not run as deep as Hubble managed to back in the day... But there are a lot of people who otherwise never think about space sharing Webb images.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to push for funding for the next great observatory, now is the time\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-23T23:42:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll believe Carl Sagan is happening when they fully fund it. Given they didn\u0027t even do LUVIOR properly, I remain skeptical.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}